# PR #11056: Fix PS66980:
**Tipo:** bugfix
**Branch:** `wip/anahi/fix-ps66980` → `feature/Improv`

## Descripción
1. Replaced the unconditional overwrite with a CASE guard that preserves the existing DB value when @PreferredLanguageId = 0 (s_enc_read_user_for_login)
2. Moved update user profile before updating from ignition DB.
3. Added missing rollback in UpdateIgnitionDBUserFields

## Feedback de reviewers
[COMMENTED por @copilot-pull-request-reviewer[bot]]: ## Pull request overview

Fixes an SSO/login user-sync issue where `PreferredLanguageId` could be unintentionally reset to `0`, and adjusts the ignition/runtime merge flow so profile-service updates are applied before the runtime user is initialised. Also adds transaction cleanup in an early-return path during ignition user updates.

**Changes:**
- Guarded `PreferredLanguageId` updates in `s_enc_read_user_for_login` so `@PreferredLanguageId = 0` preserves the DB value.
- Moved the profile-service update earlier in the ignition→runtime merge, with a post-update re-read to avoid stale runtime fields.
- Added a missing rollback for one early-return path during ignition DB user updates.

### Reviewed changes

Copilot reviewed 4 out of 4 changed files in this pull request and generated 4 comments.

| File | Description |
| ---- | ----------- |
| Core/SQL/update_db_ignition_PS-66980.sql | Adds an IgnitionMaster upgrade script that recreates `s_enc_read_user_for_login` with a CASE guard for `PreferredLanguageId`. |
| Core/SQL/base_procs_ignition.sql | Applies the same CASE guard to the canonical ignition stored proc definition. |
| Core/Business Layer/DataAccess/UserSystem.cs | Ensures an early-return path rolls back an open ignition transaction. |
| Core/Business Layer/DataAccess/AuthenticationSystem.cs | Updates merge ordering and refreshes ignition user fields before populating the runtime user. |



